m in the afternoon on Sep 11th.  Poetry is not my strong point, but I saw it laying around on my hard drive and figured it wouldn't hurt to share it.<br>
<br>
&quot;Day of Tears&quot;<br>
by A. M. Meier (Sep 11, '01)<br>
<br>
when all was over<br>
i felt only vain<br>
why was it that these lives were ended?<br>
why was it that we deserved this pain?<br>
<br>
so i look up<br>
towards the sky above<br>
and ask &quot;why?&quot; to the heavens<br>
from them i hear no love<br>
<br>
the violence rips at me<br>
digging into my flesh<br>
the pain i am feeling is<br>
only caused by death<br>
<br>
it started a normal day<br>
in the life of those in vain<br>
but when all was over<br>
nothing would be normal again<br>
<br>
the smoke billows out<br>
and covers the sky<br>
the sun hides in shame<br>
of our civilized lie<br>
<br>
what was it they thought?<br>
why was it they killed?<br>
who created this darkness<br>
that tries to engulf our world?<br>
<br>
an empty void on the horizon<br>
its old glamour, fading away<br>
ten-thousand dead and gone<br>
on what started a normal day<br>
<br>
i try to remember<br>
life before my fears<br>
before that fateful day<br>
when the sky rained tears <p><table width="*%">
